  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I am sorry to read your comments about your recent visit to the Emergency department (ED), where you identified that the standard of cleanliness was not at the level we would expect for our Department.

All staff in the ED are trained to report and action areas of concern regarding cleanliness and infection control within a reasonable time frame.  I apologise that this was not the case on this occasion.

Please be assured that the concerns you have raised are acknowledged. I will be sharing your experience with all staff so that we can learn from this with the aim of improving the future level of cleanliness in the ED.

One action that has been put in place already is for our reception staff to monitor the cleanliness of the waiting area hourly and hold a record of this and any actions.  ISS, our cleaning partners, have also been informed of your feedback.

If you would like your concerns investigated further and receive a formal response please contact the Patient Advice &amp;amp; Liaison Service (PALS) team at the Queen Elizabeth Hospital on 020 8836 4592. 

Thank you for taking the time to provide feedback.

Tracey Murphy 

Emergency Department Matron
